 <sect1 id="gkb-intro">
  <title>A GNOME billentyûzet-átkapcsoló applet</title>

  <para>
    A <application>GNOME gkb applet</application> egy kis zászlót jelenít
    meg a <interface>panel</interface>odon és semmi hasznosat nem csinál 
    vele. Mindezen felül, ha rákattintassz a zászlóra, meg tudod változtatni
    a billentyûzeted kiosztását. Ez a gnome-applets csomag része. A dokumentum 
    a gnome-applets-1.2 csomagban megjelenõ verzió leírása.
  </para>
  <para>
    It is occasionally found in the <interface>panel</interface> anyway, 
    but if you don't see it, you can start it by clicking <mousebutton>button
    3</mousebutton> on an empty part of the <interface>panel</interface>
    and following the sequence
   <menuchoice>
   <guimenu>Applets</guimenu>
    <guisubmenu>Tools</guisubmenu>
    <guimenuitem>gkb</guimenuitem>
   </menuchoice>
  </para>
  <para>
    The gkb applet was written by Szabolcs Ban (<email>shooby@gnome.hu</email>). 
    Please report bugs in it to the
    <ulink type="http" url="http://bugs.gnome.org">GNOME bug tracking 
    system</ulink>. You can do this by following the guidelines on that site 
    or by using <command>bug-buddy</command> from the command-line. 
    For the package, put gnome-core.
  </para>

  <sect2 id="gkb-usage">
   <title>Usage</title>

   <para>
    First, you need to start the properties window... TODO
   </para>

   <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
     <para>
       If you have the <application>fortune</application> package installed,
       pressing <mousebutton>mouse button 1</mousebutton> brings up a
       a <guilabel>dialogue box</guilabel> with a fortune in it. 
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Pressing <mousebutton>mouse button 2</mousebutton> and holding it
      down allows you to drag your gkb about.
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
       Pressing <mousebutton>mouse button 3</mousebutton> brings up a
       menu which includes a <guisubmenu>preferences menu</guisubmenu> and
       an <guimenuitem>About</guimenuitem> box. 
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </orderedlist>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 id="gkb-prefs">
   <title>Preferences</title>
   <para>
     The <guilabel>preferences dialogue box</guilabel> (called
     GNOME gkb Properties) is simple, with five options you can
     configure.
   </para>

   <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
     <term>Your GNOME gkb's keymap name</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
        You can change your gkb's keymap name here. The default name is us.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
     <term>The icon filename</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
        You can select a different set of pictures here. By default, 
        the list of pictures is in <filename>$PREFIX/pixmaps/gkb/</filename>,
        which you can browse and choose from. You may also put a different
        pathname in pointing to your own pictures.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

   </variablelist>
  </sect2>

  <sect2 id="gkb-bugs">
   <title>Bugs and Limitations</title>
   <para>
     No bugs known. The applet goesn't work at all.
   </para>
  </sect2>
 
